                    "value": "<p>30 feet. <strong>Requirements</strong> The Tree that Weeps isn't using Dead Tree</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> A creature that begins its turn in the aura is potentially overwhelmed with despair and must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:40] save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and is temporarily immune for 1 hour.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed] for 1 round by despair, and then @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} after recovering from paralysis.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the paralysis doesn't end automatically. A character can attempt a new Will save to end the paralysis at the end of their turn; the DC is reduced by 1 each turn that passes.</p>"
